scopecontent.p:
Contains: 
                        An Intensive Sociology: A Project
                      by Franklin H. Giddings, with a placed-in typescript entitled "The Greater Wrong"; two copies of "Can Education Humanize Civilization"; "The American Idea" by Franklin H. Giddings; "The Social and Legal Aspects of Compulsory Education and Child Labor" by Franklin H. Gidddings; 
                        The Survey
                     , Vol. LXVI, No. 8 (15 July 1931); 
                        Fortnightly Bulletin
                     , Vol. XIV, No. 3 (5 November 1926); a clipping from the Saturday Review of Literature (20 October 1928) entitled "Books of Special Interest"; "Patriotism", by Franklin H. Giddings (February 1925); 
                        City Club Bulletin
                     , Vol. V, No. 14 (16 April 1912); 
                        What Makes the General Welfare
                     , by Franklin H. Giddings (March 1912); "Which Do You Prefer?" by Franklin H. Giddings (1911); 
                        Principles of Sociology: Reading, Instructions and Summary of Theory
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1910); 
                        The Laws of Evolution
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1905); 
                        Sociological Questions
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1903); Columbia Law Review. Book Reviews. (June 1901); "Journal of Philosophy" proof.

Contains: 
                        Ethics For Real Persons
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        The Pluralistic Field and the Sample
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; two copies of 
                        The Scientific Scrutiny of Societal Facts
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        International Coinage: A Unit of Eight Grammes
                     , by Robert Noxon Toppan (1879); 
                        The Survey
                     , Vol. XXXIII, No. 6 (7 November 1914); 
                        The Classification of Societal Facts
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        The Measurement of Social Forces
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1 November 1922); 
                        The New York Herald
                      (1 April 1909).

Contains: two copies of 
                        The Relation of Social Theory to Public Policy
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (September 1912); 
                        Sociology and Political Economy
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (March 1888); 
                        The Bases of an Enduring Peace
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (April 1917); 
                        Paleontological History of the Genus Platanus
                      by Lester F. Ward (1888); 
                        The Measurement of Social Pressure
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (March 1908); 
                        Sovereignty and Government
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1906); 
                        The Place of Sociology Among the Science
                      by L. F. Ward (1895).

Contains: 
                        The Educational Value of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        Publications of the American Economic Association
                     , Vol. III, No. 1 (March 1888); 
                        Some Social and Ecomic Paradoxes
                      by Lester F. Ward (1889); 
                        Ethical Aspects of Social Science
                      by Lester F. Ward (July 1896); 
                        The Social Lynching of Gorky and Andreiva
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1906); 
                        The Relation of Social Democracy to Higher Education
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1894); 
                        Bibliography of Franklin Henry Giddings
                      (1931); 
                        Herbert Spencer's Sociology
                      by Lester F. Ward (31 March 1904).

Contains: 
                        Sociology
                      by Frankin H. Giddings (1908); 
                        The Educational Value of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1922); 
                        The Measurement of Social Forces
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1922); 
                        The Grounds of Presumption
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1922); 
                        Further Inquiries of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1921); 
                        Pluralistic Behavior
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1920); 
                        A Theory of History
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1920).

Contains: 
                        The Theory of Socialization
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1897); 
                        The Functioning of Human Society: Social Achievement
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1932); two copies of 
                        Inhabitants and Societies
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1931); 
                        Giddings, War and Small: An Interchange of Letters
                      edited by Bernhard J. Stern (1932); 
                        The Concepts and Methods of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1904); 
                        The Theory of Capital
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1890).

Contains: 
                        The Relation of Social Theory to Public Policy
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1912); 
                        Profit Sharing
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1886); 
                        The Theory of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1894); 
                        The Historical Outlook: A Journal for Readers, Students and Teachers of History
                     , Vol. XIII, No. 9 (December 1922); 
                        The Blotter
                     , Vol. III, No. 4 (1901).

Contains: 
                        Status of the Mind Problem
                      by Lester F. Ward (1894); "Reviews - PSQ June 1894 - F.H.G."; 
                        Ethics for Real Persons
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1916); 
                        The Giddings Quarter-century
                      by A. A. Tenney (1919); 
                        The American Journal of Sociology
                     , Vol. XXIV, No. 1 (1918); 
                        The Democracy of Universal Military Service
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1916); 
                        Year Book of the Empire State Society: Sons of the American Revolution 1912-1913
                      (1913); 
                        Letters of Alfred Russel Wallace to Lester F. Ward
                      by Bernhard J. Stern (1935).

Contains: 
                        Book Reviews
                     , Vol. V, No. 10 (April 1898); 
                        The Destinies of Democracy
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1897); "Ultimate Hell" poem by Franklin H. Giddings (1915); 
                        The Child as a Member of Society
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1915); 
                        The Changing Attitude Toward War: As Reflected in the American Press
                      with introduction by Franklin H. Giddings (1914); clipping from 
                        The Independent
                     , Vol. 79, No. 3426 (10 August 1914); "The Collapse of Civilization in the Next War" by Franklin H. Giddings (1918); 
                        The Christmas Message, 1917
                      by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        A Double Entry Education
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1917); 
                        Americanism in War and in Peace
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1917); 
                        The Bases of an Enduring Peace
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1917); 
                        The Ethics of Social Progress
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1893); clipping regarding "The Ethics of Socialism" by Franklin H. Giddings; 
                        The Growth of Capital and the Cause of Interest
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1891).

Contains: 
                        Outline of Lectures on Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1891); 
                        The Theory of Capital
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1890); 
                        Sociology and Political Economy
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1888); "The Divine Right of Humane Ability" address by Franklin H. Giddings (1922); 
                        The American Anthropologist
                     , Vol. X, No. I (January 1897); 
                        Journal of Applied Sociology
                     , Vol. IX, No. 5 (May-June 1925); 
                        The Province of Sociology
                      by Franklin H. Giddings (1890).
